# ── onec-mcp-universal configuration ────────────────────────────────────────

# Gateway port (default: 8080)
# GW_PORT=8080

# Log level: DEBUG, INFO, WARNING, ERROR
# LOG_LEVEL=INFO

# Structured JSON logs (false by default). Set true for log aggregation systems.
# LOG_JSON=false

# Optional bearer token for mutating HTTP API endpoints:
# /api/action/* (mutating actions), /api/register, /api/unregister, /api/export-*
# Leave empty to keep backward-compatible behavior without token auth.
# GATEWAY_API_TOKEN=change-me

# ── Linux setup ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Host path where BSL source files will be stored (subdirs created per database).
# Docker mounts this path into the gateway container as /workspace, and the same
# host path is passed to LSP containers so they can read the exported sources.
# Windows example: BSL_WORKSPACE=C:\Users\user\bsl-projects
# Linux example:   BSL_WORKSPACE=/abs/path/to/bsl-projects
# setup.sh fills this automatically with an absolute repo-local path.
# BSL_WORKSPACE=/abs/path/to/bsl-projects

# Path to 1C platform directory on host (mounted into containers)
# HOST_PLATFORM_PATH=/opt/1cv8

# Platform path for platform-context docs server
PLATFORM_PATH=/opt/1cv8/x86_64/8.3.27.2074

# ── BSL export host service ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
# URL of tools/export-host-service.py (host-side daemon). When set, the
# gateway routes BSL exports to this URL instead of running 1cv8 inside the
# container — protects 1C software licenses from hardware-fingerprint
# mismatches that can exhaust activation slots.
# setup.sh fills this automatically. Defaults are:
#   Linux   (host network):    http://localhost:8082
#   Windows (Docker Desktop):  http://host.docker.internal:8082
# EXPORT_HOST_URL=http://localhost:8082

# Internal docker-control sidecar used by the gateway for container lifecycle,
# Docker diagnostics, LSP proxying, and safe .env writes.
# setup.sh fills this automatically. Defaults are:
#   Linux   (host network):    http://localhost:8091
#   Windows/macOS (bridge):    http://docker-control:8091
# DOCKER_CONTROL_URL=http://localhost:8091

# Shared bearer token for gateway -> docker-control requests.
# setup.sh generates a strong value automatically if the key is missing.
# The dashboard masks it instead of displaying it in plain text.
# DOCKER_CONTROL_TOKEN=change-me

# Secret salt for stable anonymization mapping across gateway restarts.
# setup.sh generates a strong value automatically if the key is missing.
# The dashboard masks it instead of displaying it in plain text.
# ANONYMIZER_SALT=change-me

# Safety override (default: false). Enable only for HASP/CI environments where
# running 1cv8 DESIGNER inside Docker cannot burn software-license activations.
# Without EXPORT_HOST_URL and with this flag disabled, export_bsl_sources fails fast.
# ALLOW_CONTAINER_DESIGNER_EXPORT=false

# BSL workspace container path (advanced — leave alone unless you change the
# docker-compose volume target from /workspace to something else).
# BSL_CONTAINER_WORKSPACE=/workspace

# 1C license directory (Linux: /var/1C, mounted read-only into container)
# ONEC_LICENSES_PATH=/var/1C

# Dashboard folder browser — host filesystem exposed to the picker.
# setup.sh auto-fills these; set manually only if running without setup.sh.
#   Linux:   HOST_ROOT=/        HOSTFS_HOME=/home       HOST_ROOT_PREFIX=
#   Windows: HOST_ROOT=C:/Users/you  HOSTFS_HOME=C:/Users/you  HOST_ROOT_PREFIX=C:/Users/you
# HOST_ROOT_PREFIX is the host-side path of whatever is mounted at /hostfs inside
# the gateway — empty on Linux (root is mounted as-is), set to the user profile
# on Windows so the API can translate C:/... host paths to container paths.
# HOST_ROOT=/
# HOSTFS_HOME=/home
# HOST_ROOT_PREFIX=

# ── Windows setup ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# On Windows use the override file:
#   docker compose -f docker-compose.yml -f docker-compose.windows.yml up -d
# And run the export service on the host:
#   python tools\export-host-service.py --port 8082
#
# Platform path on Windows (comment out HOST_PLATFORM_PATH if 1C is not on Linux):
# HOST_PLATFORM_PATH=C:\Program Files\1cv8
# PLATFORM_PATH=C:\Program Files\1cv8\8.3.27.2074
#
# Disable Linux-only license mount:
# ONEC_LICENSES_PATH=./data

# ── Backends ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Comma-separated list of backends to enable.
# setup.sh automatically builds the local Java 21-compatible LSP image when
# bsl-lsp-bridge is enabled here.
# Add test-runner after starting it with: docker compose --profile test-runner up -d
# ENABLED_BACKENDS=onec-toolkit,platform-context,bsl-lsp-bridge,test-runner

# Optional pin for the local LSP image build (used by tools/build-lsp-image.sh).
# BSL_LSP_BRIDGE_REF=2b9ff1b823b679209b215e57bf5d7a47d4447a89
# BSL_LS_VERSION=0.29.0

# Test runner URL (if test-runner profile is active)
# TEST_RUNNER_URL=http://localhost:8000/sse

# BSL Graph URL (if the bundled bsl-graph profile is active)
# BSL_GRAPH_URL=http://localhost:8888

# ── 1C:Naparnik (ITS search) ───────────────────────────────────────────────
# Get API key at https://code.1c.ai (Profile → API token, requires ITS subscription)
# NAPARNIK_API_KEY=your-api-key-here

# ── Metadata cache ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# TTL in seconds for get_metadata cache (0 = disabled, default: 600)
# METADATA_CACHE_TTL=600

# ── BSL export ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Timeout in seconds for BSL export (default: 3600 = 1 hour).
# Automatically increased to 3 hours for non-localhost 1C servers.
# BSL_EXPORT_TIMEOUT=3600

# Host-side BSL workspace path (same as BSL_WORKSPACE, used for path mapping).
# Set this if BSL_WORKSPACE is a container path and differs from host path.
# BSL_HOST_WORKSPACE=/abs/path/to/bsl-projects

# 1C toolkit timeout in seconds (default: 180)
# ONEC_TIMEOUT=180

# Safe-by-default: dangerous toolkit write/exec paths require explicit opt-in.
# Applies to the static onec-toolkit container and dynamic per-DB toolkits.
# TOOLKIT_ALLOW_DANGEROUS_WITH_APPROVAL=false

# REST/dashboard rate limiting (MCP /mcp and /health are not throttled).
# GATEWAY_RATE_LIMIT_ENABLED=true
# GATEWAY_RATE_LIMIT_READ_RPM=120
# GATEWAY_RATE_LIMIT_MUTATING_RPM=30
